<subSubSection pageId="168" pageNumber="771" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="168.[706,1297,2779,3202]" pageId="168" pageNumber="771">
Taxonomic status of 
<taxonomicName box="[1013,1163,2897,2926]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lemniscomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="168" pageNumber="771" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="roseveari">L. roseveari</taxonomicName>
is uncertain. It appears to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[708,841,2976,3005]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lemniscomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="168" pageNumber="771" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griselda">L. griselda</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[912,1034,2976,3005]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lemniscomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="168" pageNumber="771" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rosalia">L. rosalia</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
